{"sequence":17,"timestamp":"2026-04-14T22:06:04.611995989Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-d6eb874a","body":"finding_summary: The patch still lets the daemon guess a run identity in `persist_workflow_run_id`, so a manual rerun between dispatch completion and persistence can stamp the newer run onto the task and bypass the new fail-closed reconciliation guard.\nseverity: high\naffected_files:\n- src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs:1779-1810\n- src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs:1941-1944\n- src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs:7797-7948\nremediation_hint: Stop deriving `workflow_run_id` from the latest `RunStarted` event. Persist the authoritative run id from the dispatch/result path or another deterministic artifact of the just-finished attempt; if that binding cannot be proven, leave the field unset so `try_reconcile_success` takes the new `reconciliation_no_run_binding` path.","dedup_key":"3f903e987e406b5f294a2e2589c15747eb6efd8810ce96e585e9f8a5d58e240a","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260414213536","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
