{"sequence":34,"timestamp":"2026-04-14T22:42:45.739174696Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-536e5340","body":"finding_summary: `persist_workflow_run_id` only updates the task record on disk, but both dispatch paths still pass the old `active_task` into `try_reconcile_success`, so newly completed tasks are guaranteed to look unbound on their first success path.\nseverity: high\naffected_files:\n- src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs\n- src/contexts/automation_runtime/task_service.rs\nremediation_hint: After `persist_workflow_run_id(...)` at `src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs:992-993` / `1682-1683`, reload the task from the store or thread the captured `run_id` directly into reconciliation before calling `try_reconcile_success`. Add an end-to-end regression test for a first-time successful run.\nevidence:\n- `src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs:1092-1093` and `1719-1720` call `try_reconcile_success(..., &active_task)` immediately after persistence.\n- `src/contexts/automation_runtime/task_service.rs:634-643` shows `set_workflow_run_id` mutates only the stored copy.\n- `src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs:1917-1920` now fail-closes whenever the in-memory task still has `workflow_run_id == None`.\nimpact: any task whose `workflow_run_id` was absent before dispatch will now be marked `reconciliation_no_run_binding` and push the milestone controller to `NeedsOperator` even when the authoritative run id was just persisted successfully.","dedup_key":"10d9045e30b85227a6d7adcbc8a69624abaabaabbc02bc3256851e47d672a91c","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260414213536","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
