{"sequence":51,"timestamp":"2026-04-14T23:12:57.313387128Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-22c03200","body":"finding_summary: The new authoritative run_id fallback bypasses the durable workflow_run_id check, so a failed set_workflow_run_id write no longer stops reconciliation.\nseverity: medium\naffected_files: [\"src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs\"]\nremediation_hint: Reload the task after persist_workflow_run_id (or make that write mandatory) and only let try_reconcile_success proceed when the durable task record actually contains workflow_run_id; do not use the transient run_id to bypass the fail-closed path.\n\nDetails: persist_workflow_run_id is still explicitly non-blocking at src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs:1772-1795, but the callers at src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs:992-994, 1092-1094, 1683-1684, and 1720-1722 now hand the in-memory run_id straight into try_reconcile_success. workflow_run_id_for_reconciliation then prefers that ephemeral value over the task's stored binding at src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs:1798-1803 and 1931-1937, and the new test at src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs:8050-8174 locks in that behavior. If the store write fails and a later mark_completed/label-sync step fails at src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs:1145-1155 or 1747-1748, the daemon has already closed/synced the bead and updated milestone lineage even though the task still lacks a durable task-to-run binding. That violates the bead's fail-closed contract and leaves the retry path in an operator-only state after partial success bookkeeping has already happened.","dedup_key":"515b3b3c8ff3ec9f7808fcdadfe39e2c394a280a723b9c022b2a124b173cff1d","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260414213536","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
